22/02/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Monday (21 February) named Atilla Koc as new culture and tourism minister, following Erkan Mumcu's resignation earlier this month.
The nomination was announced after a meeting between Erdogan and President Ahmet Necdet Sezer.
Also Monday, parliament member Suleyman Saribas of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP), resigned from the party caucus.
He cited serious differences with the AKP leadership.
(NTV, AFP, TurkishPress.com - 21/02/05)
